<emphasis box="[294,626,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Elaphropeza xanthocephala</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi M." box="[636,782,1963,1989]" firstAuthor="Bezzi" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturalies Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="442 - 495" part="10" refId="ref10454" refString="Bezzi M. 1912. Rhagionidae et Empididae ex Insula Formosa a Clar. H. Sauter Missae. Annales Historico-Naturalies Musei Nationalis Hungarici 10: 442 - 495." title="Rhagionidae et Empididae ex Insula Formosa a Clar. H. Sauter Missae" type="journal article" year="1912">Bezzi, 1912</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, habitus, RBINS (leg. C. Taylor and U. Chang; photo C. Locatelli).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1399,267,329]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
TERMINALIA. Pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[494,584,267,294]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1960,1986]" captionTargetBox="[229,1385,1221,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,1194,1917]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 15. Elaphropeza xanthocephala Bezzi, 1912, male terminalia, RBINS (leg. C. Taylor and U. Chang). A. Right epandrial lamella. B. Epandrium, dorsal view. C. Left surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3476143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3476143/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Right epandrial lamella bearing two strong, flattened brown setae (
<figureCitation box="[198,307,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1960,1986]" captionTargetBox="[229,1385,1221,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,1194,1917]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 15. Elaphropeza xanthocephala Bezzi, 1912, male terminalia, RBINS (leg. C. Taylor and U. Chang). A. Right epandrial lamella. B. Epandrium, dorsal view. C. Left surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3476143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3476143/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
