</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,303,469,495]" box="[189,303,469,495]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,469,495]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,469,495]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1398,515,577]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1912" box="[189,525,515,541]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocephala">
<emphasis box="[189,525,515,541]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Elaphropeza xanthocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the single species with a yellow occiput occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1254,1398,516,542]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
mangroves and hence easy to recognize.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1399,616,713]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
In his description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi M." box="[407,559,616,642]" firstAuthor="Bezzi" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturalies Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="442 - 495" part="10" refId="ref10454" refString="Bezzi M. 1912. Rhagionidae et Empididae ex Insula Formosa a Clar. H. Sauter Missae. Annales Historico-Naturalies Musei Nationalis Hungarici 10: 442 - 495." title="Rhagionidae et Empididae ex Insula Formosa a Clar. H. Sauter Missae" type="journal article" year="1912">Bezzi (1912)</bibRefCitation>
writes that the metapleura is shining black and in the diagnosis that the metanotum is black. In our specimen the metapleura is entirely yellow and the metanotum is black. We suspect this is a lapsus or that Bezzi referred to the hypopleuron, which has an apical black spot.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1398,752,813]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi M." box="[189,341,752,778]" firstAuthor="Bezzi" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturalies Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="442 - 495" part="10" refId="ref10454" refString="Bezzi M. 1912. Rhagionidae et Empididae ex Insula Formosa a Clar. H. Sauter Missae. Annales Historico-Naturalies Musei Nationalis Hungarici 10: 442 - 495." title="Rhagionidae et Empididae ex Insula Formosa a Clar. H. Sauter Missae" type="journal article" year="1912">Bezzi (1912)</bibRefCitation>
had only a single specimen from Takao which is located at the coast and it is not unlikely that this specimen was collected in the mangrove of Takao.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
